Performing magic or witchcraft was a capital offense in many societies until relatively recently. Definitely a way to have your reputation go through the floor if accused - it was also one of those offenses where there was generally a presumption of guilt until innocence could be proven. And proving yourself incapable of performing magic usually involved dying (if I toss you in a river and you don't drown, you're a witch; if I toss you in a river and you do drown, you aren't).







